<item>
            <title>[LU-16011] LNet selftest should use a preallocated bulk on the server side.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16011</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cray testing have show an LST limited with 35Gb/s 1M bulk transfers with 3 rail server and 16 HDR clients. During profile, I found a LST is cpu bound with page cache operations, because server side don&apos;t have an preallocated bulk&apos;s for transfers.&lt;br/&gt;
Once preallocation done - server able to achieve a wire speed - 73 Gb/s with very low cpu power.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;LNet Bandwidth of servers]
[R] Avg: 11.28    MB/s  Min: 11.28    MB/s  Max: 11.28    MB/s
[W] Avg: 73949.30 MB/s  Min: 73949.30 MB/s  Max: 73949.30 MB/s
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
